FOROBA BLON README

Access the admin interface over the local WiFi network:
http://192.168.5.1/admin




How to set up foroba blon:
1. Follow the existing documentation to set up a KasaDaka system.
2. Checkout the foroba-blon github branch
3. Give everybody rights to read and write in the /tmp directory:
	sudo chmod -R 777 /tmp
4. Create the directory to save user recordings: 
	mkdir html/audio/user_recordings
	sudo chmod -R 777 html/audio/user_recordings
5. Upload the included .ttl file to ClioPatria (port 3020), name the graph according to the config.py (http://localhost/foroba-blon)
6. In the ClioPatria web interface, grant all rights to the anonymous user. (Admin>Users>anonymous>edit)
7. Restart all relevant services:
	sudo /etc/init.d/apache2 restart
	sudo /etc/init.d/openvxi restart
	sudo /etc/init.d/asterisk restart
8. Install sox
	sudo apt-get install sox


NOTES:
Currently the language is hardcoded to French.
Messages are currently limited to 60 seconds.


INTERFACE WAV FILES REQUIRED:
speakYourMessage.wav
endRecordingWithAnyPress.wav
press1ToConfirm.wav
press2ToRetry.wav
insertMessageSuccess.wav
(in the required language dir: /hmtl/audio/fr/interface/xxx.wav)


